+/*
+ * coderyoMC — per-entity-type LOD policy class.
+ *
+ * The per-entity-type policy is the main guard that makes LOD/DAB plausibly default-on: the classic
+ * DAB contraption complaint (villager breeders, farm-animal breeding/cooldown cadence, mob-farm
+ * timing) is overwhelmingly about TIMING-SENSITIVE passive/utility entities, NOT hostile combat AI.
+ * So we split entities into policy classes and apply LOD aggressiveness per class:
+ *
+ *   HOSTILE  -> throttle aggressively far away (the big, low-gameplay-risk win).
+ *   PASSIVE  -> throttle very conservatively (gentle divisors, NEAR + an extra full-rate band).
+ *   EXEMPT   -> never throttle (timing-sensitive / player-attached / persistent entities).
+ *
+ * See pathfinding-elision-design.md §2.1 / §8 (the DAB timing-sensitivity hazard).
+ */
+package com.coderyo.lod;
+
+/**
+ * The LOD policy class an entity belongs to. Determines how aggressively the L0 DAB throttle (and the
+ * extended far-entity throttle) may slow a mob's AI when it is far from any player.
+ *
+ * <p>Classification is performed by {@link LodPolicy#classify}; the per-class aggressiveness is read
+ * from {@link LodConfig} so it is tunable without a rebuild.
+ */
+public enum LodEntityClass {
+    /**
+     * Hostile / monster AI (zombies, skeletons, creepers, …). The big LOD win and the lowest
+     * gameplay risk: their far-away "think slower" drift is imperceptible and they run no
+     * timing-sensitive contraption logic. Eligible for the full divisor table AND the extended
+     * far-entity throttle (look/sensor/non-essential behavior coarsening).
+     */
+    HOSTILE,
+
+    /**
+     * Passive / farm animals and other creatures that are NOT exempt. Throttled only very
+     * conservatively: a gentle divisor and an extra full-rate band, never the extended throttle.
+     * This keeps breeding/cooldown cadence within the error standard's Tier-3 floor (>=95% of
+     * vanilla cadence inside the full-rate radius) while still saving some far-away AI cost.
+     */
+    PASSIVE,
+
+    /**
+     * Never throttled — full vanilla cadence at every distance. Reserved for entities whose exact
+     * AI timing is gameplay-load-bearing or that are attached to a player:
+     * villagers (breeders / trades), tamed / named / persistence-required mobs, vehicles, leashed or
+     * ridden entities, and anything a player is riding or recently interacted with. This is the
+     * mob-farm / villager-breeder contraption guard.
+     */
+    EXEMPT;
+
+    /** True if this class is allowed to be throttled at all (HOSTILE or PASSIVE). */
+    public boolean throttleable() {
+        return this != EXEMPT;
+    }
+}
